KOKO EATING BANANAS
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Koko loves to eat bananas.

• piles[i] = number of bananas in ith pile
• guards return in h hours

Koko chooses an eating speed k bananas/hour.

Rules:
• Each hour she picks ONE pile
• Eats k bananas from that pile
• If pile < k → eats all and stops for that hour

Goal:
Find the minimum k such that all bananas are eaten within h hours.


Example 1:

Input:
piles = [3,6,7,11]
h = 8

Output:
4


Example 2:

Input:
piles = [30,11,23,4,20]
h = 5

Output:
30


Example 3:

Input:
piles = [30,11,23,4,20]
h = 6

Output:
23


Constraints:

1 <= piles.length <= 10^4  
piles.length <= h <= 10^9  
1 <= piles[i] <= 10^9



────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
BINARY SEARCH ON ANSWER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Search range:

minimum speed = sum(piles) / h  
maximum speed = max(piles)



class Solution {
public:
    int minEatingSpeed(vector<int>& piles, int h)
    {
        int strt = 0, end = 0;
        double mid;

        long long sum = 0;

        for(int i = 0; i < piles.size(); i++)
        {
            sum += piles[i];
            end = max(end, piles[i]);
        }

        strt = sum / h;

        int ans;

        while(strt <= end)
        {
            mid = strt + (end - strt) / 2;

            double count = 0;

            for(int i = 0; i < piles.size(); i++)
            {
                count += ceil(piles[i] / double(mid));
            }

            if(count <= h)
            {
                ans = mid;
                end = mid - 1;
            }
            else
            {
                strt = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
};
